Sounds like you have not configured enough xmx memory for the JMeter process.  You can set the amount of memory allocated to the process in the configuration settings for the plugin like this:

    &lt;configuration&gt;
      &lt;jMeterProcessJVMSettings&gt;
        &lt;xms&gt;1024&lt;/xms&gt;
        &lt;xmx&gt;1024&lt;/xmx&gt;
        &lt;arguments&gt;
          &lt;argument&gt;-Xprof&lt;/argument&gt;
          &lt;argument&gt;-Xfuture&lt;/argument&gt;
        &lt;/arguments&gt;
      &lt;/jMeterProcessJVMSettings&gt;
    &lt;/configuration&gt;

Link to the wiki that describes this is: https://github.com/jmeter-maven-plugin/jmeter-maven-plugin/wiki/Configuring-the-jvm-that-the-jmeter-process-runs-in

